theorem Topology.dense_of_denseInterior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense (interior A) → Dense (A : Set X) := by
  intro hDenseInt
  -- The closure of `interior A` is the whole space.
  have h_closureInt : closure (interior A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) :=
    hDenseInt.closure_eq
  -- `closure (interior A)` is contained in `closure A`.
  have h_subset :
      closure (interior A : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) :=
    closure_mono (interior_subset : interior A ⊆ A)
  -- Hence `closure A` must also be the whole space.
  have h_closureA_eq : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    refine
      (Set.Subset.antisymm ?_ ?_) <;>
    try intro x hx
    · simp
    ·
      have : (x : X) ∈ closure (A : Set X) := by
        have : (x : X) ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
          simp
        simpa [h_closureInt] using h_subset this
      simpa using this
  -- Conclude that `A` is dense.
  exact (dense_iff_closure_eq).2 h_closureA_eq

theorem Topology.dense_implies_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense (A : Set X) → Topology.P3 (A : Set X) := by
  intro hDense
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  -- `closure A` is the whole space since `A` is dense.
  have h_closure : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := hDense.closure_eq
  intro x hxA
  -- After rewriting, the goal becomes membership in `interior (Set.univ)`, which is trivial.
  have : (x : X) ∈ interior (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simp
  simpa [h_closure, interior_univ] using this

theorem Topology.P3_closure_of_dense
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense (A : Set X) → Topology.P3 (closure (A : Set X)) := by
  intro hDense
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x hx
  -- Since `A` is dense, its closure is the whole space.
  have h_closure_eq : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) :=
    hDense.closure_eq
  -- Hence every point lies in the interior of this closure (and of its
  -- further closure, which is equal to itself).
  have : (x : X) ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simp
  simpa [closure_closure, h_closure_eq, interior_univ] using this
